                           <q xml:lang="en"/> The note is written in pencil, it states that Asgädom
                           Ṣaʾǝdu donated the book to the church of Abunä Täklä Haymanot (ʾAraʿro
                           Täklä Haymanot). </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- King Ḫaylä Śǝllase and Metropolitan Basǝlyos are
                           mentioned in the supplication formula on fol. 52vb.&#xD; - Spaces for
                           rubricated names were left unfilled throughout the Ms.&#xD; - Illegible
                           notes written in pen and pencil: fol. 3r.&#xD; - Scribbles in the margin:
                           fols. 27r, 59r.&#xD; - Lacunas: fols. 37vb, 38vb, 41rb, 42rb, 43rab,
                           43rab, 44ra.&#xD; - Single Ethiopic letters or numerals are written in
                           the upper margin: fols. 9r, 11r, 15r, 21r, 22v, 23v, 26v, 34v, 42r,
                           47v.</item>
